entry.title: win: Remove dcheck in GetDisplayInfosFromSystem
entry.content:
The DCHECK asserts that GetSystemMetrics (SM_CMONITORS) ==

the number of monitors encountered by EnumDisplayMonitors.

This dcheck was added in https://codereview.chromium.org/1639623003.



Per MSDN, EnumDisplayMonitors can return pseudo monitors but

GetSystemMetrics (SM_CMONITORS) counts only the display monitors. I

don't think that's generally what's triggering this dcheck, but it

seems Windows makes no guarantees these two counts are the same.

entry.title: dlp: Get ScopedFileAccess before opening zip files
entry.content:
Currently we are only getting a scoped file access object before the

unzip operation starts. However, the zip file might be opened in other

cases just for accessing its metadata.

With this CL, we acquire a scoped file access object directly in an

extract IO task so that we are sure the zip files are accessible for the

all duration of the extraction task.

This also has the advantage of making a single DBUS call to the DLP

daemon to get a scoped file access object for all N zipped files instead

of making N calls, one for every file.

entry.title: printing: Fix primary user profile access
entry.content:
CupsProxyServiceManager is KeyedService and is created during

profile loading. It creates CupsProxyServiceDelegateImpl when

CupsProxyClient thinks underlying dbus service is available.

CupsProxyServiceDelegateImpl reaches for primary user profile

in it constructor. There is a race between profile finish

loading and dbus service availability. When dbus availability

is signaled earlier than profile loading, DumpWithoutCrashing in

ProfileManager::GetPrimaryUserProfile would be hit.



Since CupsProxyServiceManager is a KeyedService and knows the

profile, we don't have to reach out to ProfileManager to get it.

This CL does the following:

- Create CupsProxyServiceManager only for the primary user profile;

- Pass down Profile explicitly to CupsProxyServiceDelegateImpl;

entry.title: TextFinder annotations fail to find clipped content
entry.content:
This CL makes it so that TextFinder type annotations will fail to attach

to text if it's within an empty, overflow-clipping ancestor.

TextIterator already applies a similar exception so that even if we

attach the highlight isn't created.



The motivation for this is that this is how collapsible sections on

sites are often implemented and it's a failure if we scroll to a

highlight that cannot be seen.



This is a special-case fix for the TextFinder type. The issue applies

more generally to scroll-to-text but changes there will require more

thought and spec edits. In the mean time, this change will fix the issue

for kTextFinder type annotations and we can tweak this easily to inform

a more general solution.

entry.title: Re-enable Flake Endorser on CQ Android
entry.content:
This change re-enables Flake Endorser for Android. This is part 2 of 3.



Flake Endorser was previously disabled on these builders due to a high

false positive rate, impacting users as it was repeating tests that

were unrelated to their patchset.



ResultDB Test Results optionally allow tests to upload a file path

as part of its metadata, associating a specific test to a file.

Most of Chrome have this being set.



In crrev/c/4628558, Flake Endorser utilizes that by checking that new

tests with a file path defined have that file path being modified

as part of the patchset. If not, it's skipped. If file path is not

defined, it's included, but re-verified through the TestHistory RPC call.

entry.title: [Idle Timeout] Fix activation issues with the bubble
entry.content:
IdleBubble has several issues relating to focus/activation:



(a) The bubble activates itself despite being informative. This can

disrupt what the user is trying to do.

(b) The bubble displays when a Browser activates. It activates

itself in the middle of another widget's activation, which causes

re-entrancy issues. See state transition diagram:

https://i.imgur.com/9bcWpxe.png

(c) The ShowOnStartup pref is reset when the bubble is *displayed*,

not dismissed. Combined with (a), you can end up in a state where

the bubble is currently visible, but ShowOnStartup=true. When you

dismiss the bubble, a *new* identical bubble is displayed.

(d) If the bubble is already visible, we stack another bubble on top

of it. This is unintentional/buggy.



Fix (a) and (b) by using ShowInactive() instead of Show(). IdleBubble

doesn't grab focus on display.



Fix (c) by resetting ShowOnStartup when the bubble is dismissed.

New state transition diagram: https://i.imgur.com/pLVNswE.png



Fix (d) by adding a guard in ShowIdleBubble().

entry.title: [ios] Optimise storage of "pinned" status of WebState
entry.content:
The WebStateList used a boolean in each WebStateWrapper to store whether

the WebState is pinned, and at the same time maintain the invariant that

all pinned WebStates are at the beginning of the list.



This means that the same information is duplicated (both in the boolean

and in the position). This could lead to bugs if there is divergence of

the information.



Instead it is possible to only store the number of pinned WebStates and

to check the status for an individual WebState by comparing this index

to the counter.



This optimisation is also used by the new serialisation code to save as

described at go/bling-session-restoration.

entry.title: [@scope] Support various at-rules within @scope
entry.content:
This CL adds support for the following rules within @scope:



- @container

- @layer

- @media

- @starting-style

- @supports



Style rules within these rules are now scoped [1] to the enclosing

@scope (if any).



All at-rules are supposed to be allowed within @scope,

including rules which do not contain style rules in their body

(e.g. @property) [2], but this CL only deals with rules that

are valid "nested group rules" [3]. WPT coverage of other at-rules

is tracked by Issue 1450473.



Unlike nesting, @scope does not support declarations directly

within its body. Since we're calling CSSParserImpl::ConsumeLayer

(etc) with a non-nullptr parent_rule_for_nesting also in the @scope

case (since & needs to point to the scoping root), the condition

to enter direct-declaration parsing has been changed to check

nesting_type rather than parent_rule_for_nesting.



Additionally, for @layer, two tweaks were needed:



- Propagate nesting_type: this was just neglected earlier.

- Allow @layer *statements* within @scope: all at-rules

are supposed to be valid within @scope.



[1] https://drafts.csswg.org/css-cascade-6/#scoped-style-rules

[2] https://drafts.csswg.org/css-cascade-6/#scope-scope

[3] https://drafts.csswg.org/css-nesting-1/#nested-group-rules



Fixed: 1451088

entry.title: Split CascadeExpansion callbacks.
entry.content:
CascadeExpansion handles the case of custom and non-custom properties

separately, then combines them into one callback (taking in

CSSPropertyName), which then promptly splits them up again into

custom and non-custom properties taking different paths.



This doesn't make sense; simply split the two callbacks. Further

down the line, _maybe_ will also help us getting rid of the lookup

into the CSSProperty array, since the callbacks now no longer need

to take in the CSSProperty object.
